text: Henri Maïdou (born 14 February 1936) is a Central African retired politician. He was the Prime Minister of the Central African Empire (Central African Republic) from 14 July 1978 to 26 September 1979, and Vice President of the Central African Republic from 26 September 1979 to 22 August 1980. ==References== Category:1936 births Category:Living people Category:Prime ministers of the Central African Republic
